    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Under the Minimal profile binding, the credibility assessment for the Morrison COU2 VAD hemolysis prediction is accepted with acknowledged gaps. All 13 credibility factors have been evaluated against the project requirements documented in the regulatory submission package. Seven factors were formally assessed; six factors remain as epistemic gaps at MRL 5. The Monte Carlo UQ provides partial uncertainty characterization. Acceptance is conditional on gap closure prior to final regulatory submission, consistent with the Low assurance level designation and the project requirements for iterative credibility development.",
